          <p>Finally the word is getting out that exercise is only marginally important to overall health and inconsequential regarding weight loss.  Just b/c some people enjoy exercise doesn&#8217;t mean it&#8217;s good for everyone.</p>
<p>I think that there is no genetic propensity towards high or low metabolism.  That&#8217;s a red herring.  The real propensity is eating for comfort.  Some people eat whenever they feel bad or have a problem.  It&#8217;s as good a distraction as overworking or some drug and it&#8217;ll harm you in the long wrong like all distractions.  The genes dictate what distraction you naturally gravitate towards &#8211; this metabolism stuff is silly.</p>
