          <p>ok&#8230; I just discovered your blog and you&#8217;ve piqued my interest with this post.  you make some fair arguments, some of which I&#8217;d agree with.  do you also have a SOLUTION in mind?  like it or not, people &#8220;want&#8221; to lose weight.  </p>
<p>referring to your previous post, &#8220;8 practical steps&#8230;&#8221;, I&#8217;d challenge your adivce to &#8220;work your ass off&#8221;.  Working harder at something that won&#8217;t work won&#8217;t make it work better (say that 3x real fast!)</p>
<p>Maybe the &#8217;solution&#8217; is to change the frame of reference from which we measure success?</p>
<p>I even argue that THERE IS NO OBESITY PROBLEM.  Too much weight is simply a SYMPTOM of doing too much of the wrong thing. (or to put it differently, not doing enough of the RIGHT things).</p>
<p>Anyway, just wanted to say I enjoy your blog.  Thanks for providing this food-for-thought.  :-)</p>
