          <p>Widespread obesity is a recent problem.  It&#8217;s fairly well established that obesity is not, for the most part, a genetic problem.  Obesity has skyrocketed as people have become more sedentary and switched to high-sugar, high-fat foods.  The idea that a suddenly widespread problem is primarily genetic in nature makes no sense, unless 65% of all Americans now how this genetic problem.</p>
<p>Metabolism and obesity are separate issues.  Low metabolism is only a problem if you&#8217;re eating the same number of calories as someone with a high metabolism, and in that case, the real problem is that you are eating too much.</p>
        </li>
                        <li id="comment-291">
