          <p>Paul, yes, in sufficient quantity, exercise will cause you to lose weight.  Anyone who disputes that is an idiot.  But it takes a lot of exercise (compared to modern habits) to offset relatively small calorie excesses.</p>
<p>Certainly, exercise is a great way to lose weight, but it&#8217;s naive to believe that modern lifestyle is going to drastically change in a manner than encourages significant exercise.  It&#8217;s more realistic to target the other end of the equation, where change is easier (and a lot less time-demanding).</p>
<p>The fact that massive exercise is impractical and people won’t do it is <em>exactly</em> the point.  You&#8217;re trying to argue away human nature.</p>
